<h2>Joseph Stalin</h2>
<p>Joseph Stalin was a part of the Bolshevik Revolution that transformed Russia into the Soviet Union. He took over as dictator after the death of Vladimir Lenin. Stalin destroyed all those he believed were against him. Stalin had his main opponent, Leon Trotsky from the Soviet Union and eventually assassinated. Stalin turned the Soviet Union in totalitarian state. In this form of government, a dictatorship controls and regulates e aspect of the lives of its citizens. Stalin's police arrested millions and had them shot or sent to labor camps. He brought all factories and farms under government control. Stalin used propaganda to make himself a hero. His pictures appeared everywhere. Stalin also censored, or withheld, news from inside and outside the Soviet Union. Stalin used his power to move the Soviets to a strong industrialized economy. His government made all economic decisions to increase industry and farming. They set production goals, forcing Russians to work day and night. Workers who did not meet their production goals were punished. While production levels went up, most Russians were poor. Their standard of living and spirits were low.</p>
